message.content: Let the numerator of the fraction be $x$. The denominator is then $3x-7$. Since the fraction is equivalent to $\frac{2}{5}$, $\frac{x}{3x-7}=\frac{2}{5}$. Cross-multiplying gives $5x=2(3x-7)$. Expanding the right side gives $5x=6x-14$. Subtracting $5x$ from both sides gives $0=x-14$, so $x=\boxed{14}$.
